descr: "The Library resource is a general-purpose container for knowledge asset definitions. It can be used to describe and expose existing knowledge assets such as logic libraries and information model descriptions, as well as to describe a collection of knowledge assets."

fields.name: resourceType
fields.descr: "This is a Library resource"

fields.name: url
fields.descr: "An absolute URI that is used to identify this library when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this library is (or will be) published. The URL SHOULD include the major version of the library. For more information see [Technical and Business Versions](resource.html#versions)."

fields.name: _url
fields.descr: "Extensions for url"

fields.name: identifier
fields.descr: "A formal identifier that is used to identify this library when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. e.g. CMS or NQF identifiers for a measure artifact. Note that at least one identifier is required for non-experimental active artifacts."

fields.name: version
fields.descr: "The identifier that is used to identify this version of the library when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the library author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it might be a timestamp (e.g. yyyymmdd) if a managed version is not available. There is also no expectation that versions can be placed in a lexicographical sequence. To provide a version consistent with the Decision Support Service specification, use the format Major.Minor.Revision (e.g. 1.0.0). For more information on versioning knowledge assets, refer to the Decision Support Service specification. Note that a version is required for non-experimental active artifacts."

fields.name: _version
fields.descr: "Extensions for version"

fields.name: name
fields.descr: "A natural language name identifying the library. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation."

fields.name: _name
fields.descr: "Extensions for name"

fields.name: title
fields.descr: "A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the library."

fields.name: _title
fields.descr: "Extensions for title"

fields.name: status
fields.descr: "The status of this library. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content."

fields.name: _status
fields.descr: "Extensions for status"

fields.name: experimental
fields.descr: "A boolean value to indicate that this library is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage."

fields.name: _experimental
fields.descr: "Extensions for experimental"

fields.name: type
fields.descr: "Identifies the type of library such as a Logic Library, Model Definition, Asset Collection, or Module Definition."

fields.name: date
fields.descr: "The date  (and optionally time) when the library was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the library changes."

fields.name: _date
fields.descr: "Extensions for date"

fields.name: publisher
fields.descr: "The name of the individual or organization that published the library."

fields.name: _publisher
fields.descr: "Extensions for publisher"

fields.name: description
fields.descr: "A free text natural language description of the library from a consumer's perspective."

fields.name: _description
fields.descr: "Extensions for description"

fields.name: purpose
fields.descr: "Explaination of why this library is needed and why it has been designed as it has."

fields.name: _purpose
fields.descr: "Extensions for purpose"

fields.name: usage
fields.descr: "A detailed description of how the library is used from a clinical perspective."

fields.name: _usage
fields.descr: "Extensions for usage"

fields.name: approvalDate
fields.descr: "The date on which the resource content was approved by the publisher. Approval happens once when the content is officially approved for usage."

fields.name: _approvalDate
fields.descr: "Extensions for approvalDate"

fields.name: lastReviewDate
fields.descr: "The date on which the resource content was last reviewed. Review happens periodically after approval, but doesn't change the original approval date."

fields.name: _lastReviewDate
fields.descr: "Extensions for lastReviewDate"

fields.name: effectivePeriod
fields.descr: "The period during which the library content was or is planned to be in active use."

fields.name: useContext
fields.descr: "The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate library instances."

fields.name: jurisdiction
fields.descr: "A legal or geographic region in which the library is intended to be used."

fields.name: topic
fields.descr: "Descriptive topics related to the content of the library. Topics provide a high-level categorization of the library that can be useful for filtering and searching."

fields.name: contributor
fields.descr: "A contributor to the content of the library, including authors, editors, reviewers, and endorsers."

fields.name: contact
fields.descr: "Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher."

fields.name: copyright
fields.descr: "A copyright statement relating to the library and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the library."

fields.name: _copyright
fields.descr: "Extensions for copyright"

fields.name: relatedArtifact
fields.descr: "Related artifacts such as additional documentation, justification, or bibliographic references."

fields.name: parameter
fields.descr: "The parameter element defines parameters used by the library."

fields.name: dataRequirement
fields.descr: "Describes a set of data that must be provided in order to be able to successfully perform the computations defined by the library."

fields.name: content
fields.descr: "The content of the library as an Attachment. The content may be a reference to a url, or may be directly embedded as a base-64 string. Either way, the contentType of the attachment determines how to interpret the content."
